auth

public TransactionAuthReturn auth(java.lang.String srd,
                                  int minChargebackProbability,
                                  java.lang.Boolean sendEmailNotification,
                                  java.lang.String campaignCode,
                                  java.lang.Boolean dryrun)
                           throws VindiciaReturnException,
                                  VindiciaServiceException
Perform an auth operation on a transaction. The transaction object should be filled out with all available information, then this method is called to actually perform the action. This method has the following output return values:

'400:Must specify transaction to authorize' if no transaction specified
'400:No Account or PaymentMethod information' if neither account nor payment method is specified
'400:Amount negative' if the amount on the transaction is less than zero
'400:Vindicia fault VIN_XXX encountered.' if an internal error with the Vindicia payment system was encountered
'403:Denied' if the chargback probability is greater than minChargebackProbability
'404:Unable to load Account' if the specified account may not be loaded by VID or merchantAccountId
'405:Account has no default payment method' if the specified account is loaded, but no default payment method is available and none is explicitly provided with the transaction
'408:Required tax service temporarily unavailable.' if the tax service is temporarily unavailable

It will return 200 in all other cases, with the result of the transaction processing in the dtlink=transactionStatus field. The returned transaction will have all respective fields filled out. There is, in general, little validation of the specific values, as all that is completely necessary is an amount and PaymentMethod information, either given explicitly or gotten implicitly from the account. The majority of the remaining information is either useful for fraud prevention or for later disputation of fraudulent chargebacks.

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
minChargebackProbability - If Chargeback Probability from risk scoring is greater than this, the transaction auth will fail. Default is 100 (all transactions succeed).
sendEmailNotification - Flag indicating whether an email notification should be sent upon capture of this transaction. The email notification will be sent if a template for the preferred language and corresponding email notification type is uploaded in Vindicia database as a part of merchant configuration.
campaignCode - Optional coupon or promotion code, used to obtain a discount on this Transaction
dryrun - If "dryrun" is true, all computations will be done, but no result from this operation will be recorded in Vindicia's database.
Returns:
TransactionAuthReturn - custom return bean class for this method
Throws:
VindiciaReturnException - for non-200 return codes from Vindicia
VindiciaServiceException

authCapture

public TransactionAuthCaptureReturn authCapture(java.lang.String srd,
                                                java.lang.Boolean sendEmailNotification,
                                                java.lang.Boolean ignoreAvsPolicy,
                                                java.lang.Boolean ignoreCvnPolicy,
                                                java.lang.String campaignCode,
                                                java.lang.Boolean dryrun,
                                                int minChargebackProbability)
                                         throws VindiciaReturnException,
                                                VindiciaServiceException
Perform an auth and capture operation on a transaction. The transaction object should be filled out with all available information, then this method is called to actually perform the action. This method has the following output return values:

'400:Must specify transaction to authorize' if no transaction specified
'400:No Account or PaymentMethod information' if neither account nor payment method is specified
'400:Amount negative' if the amount on the transaction is less than zero
'400:Vindicia fault VIN_XXX encountered.' if an internal error with the Vindicia payment system was encountered
'404:Unable to load Account' if the specified account may not be loaded by VID or merchantAccountId
'405:Account has no default payment method' if the specified account is loaded, but no default payment method is available and none is explicitly provided with the transaction
'407:AVS policy evaluation failed
'408:CVN policy evaluation failed
'408:Required tax service temporarily unavailable.' if the tax service is temporarily unavailable
'409:AVS and CVN policy evaluations failed
'410:AVS and CVN policy evaluations could not be performed

It will return 200 in all other cases, with the result of the transaction processing in the dtlink=transactionStatus field. The returned transaction will have all respective fields filled out. There is, in general, little validation of the specific values, as all that is completely necessary is an amount and PaymentMethod information, either given explicitly or gotten implicitly from the account. The majority of the remaining information is either useful for fraud prevention or for later disputation of fraudulent chargebacks.

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
sendEmailNotification - Flag indicating whether an email notification should be sent upon success. The email notification will be sent if a template for the preferred language and corresponding email notification type is uploaded in Vindicia database as a part of merchant configuration.
ignoreAvsPolicy - Set to 1, to not evaluate any custom or default avs policy.
ignoreCvnPolicy - Set to 1, to not evaluate any custom or default cvn policy.
campaignCode - Optional coupon or promotion code, used to obtain a discount on this Transaction
dryrun - If "dryrun" is true, all computations will be done, but no result from this operation will be recorded in Vindicia's database.
minChargebackProbability - If Chargeback Probability from risk scoring is greater than this, the transaction auth will fail. Default is 100 (all transactions succeed).
Returns:
TransactionAuthCaptureReturn - custom return bean class for this method
Throws:
VindiciaReturnException - for non-200 return codes from Vindicia
VindiciaServiceException

calculateSalesTax

public TransactionCalculateSalesTaxReturn calculateSalesTax(java.lang.String srd)
                                                     throws VindiciaReturnException,
                                                            VindiciaServiceException
Calculates the sales tax of the referred transaction. In order to function, at a bare minimum, the amount and one address must be available. Either the shipping address may be explicitly filled out, or the billing address may be loaded from the customer account (if any). If both are available, the shipping address is used in preference. This method has the following output return values:

'400:Must specify transaction to calculate sales tax' if no transaction specified
'400:Amount negative' if the amount on the transaction is less than zero
'404:Unable to load Account' if the specified account may not be loaded by VID or merchantAccountId

It will return 200 in all other cases.

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
Returns:
TransactionCalculateSalesTaxReturn - custom return bean class for this method
Throws:
VindiciaReturnException - for non-200 return codes from Vindicia
VindiciaServiceException

capture

public static TransactionCaptureReturn capture(java.lang.String srd,
                                               Transaction[] transactions)
                                        throws VindiciaReturnException,
                                               VindiciaServiceException
Captures the specified transaction(s) from a previous auth-only. This method is used to capture the transaction at a later date (say, when inventory is available to be shipped, or after manual review of a fraud screen). If the previous auth has expired, this method may silently re-auth the transaction, as appropriate.

'200:Ok' - Call succeeded, examine the array of dtlink=CaptureResult to determine success or failure of capture
'400:Must Specify Transaction' if no transaction is specified to load

It will return 200 in all other cases.

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
transactions - An array of dtlink=Transaction objects
Returns:
TransactionCaptureReturn - custom return bean class for this method
Throws:
VindiciaReturnException - for non-200 return codes from Vindicia
VindiciaServiceException

                                        throws VindiciaReturnException,
                                               VindiciaServiceException
Captures the specified transaction(s) from a previous auth-only. This method is used to capture the transaction at a later date (say, when inventory is available to be shipped, or after manual review of a fraud screen). If the previous auth has expired, this method may silently re-auth the transaction, as appropriate.

'200:Ok' - Call succeeded, examine the array of dtlink=CaptureResult to determine success or failure of capture
'400:Must Specify Transaction' if no transaction is specified to load

It will return 200 in all other cases.

fetchByPaymentMethod

public static Transaction[] fetchByPaymentMethod(java.lang.String srd,
                                                 PaymentMethod paymentMethod,
                                                 int page,
                                                 int pageSize)
                                          throws VindiciaReturnException,
                                                 VindiciaServiceException
This method will return a list of transactions that have the specified payment method associated with them. The The input PaymentMethod object need not be fully populated. If VID is specified in the input PaymentMethod object, it will be used as the primary identifying factor for the payment method record to be used as the search criterion. If VID is not specified in the input PaymentMethod object, merchantPaymentMethodId will be used as the primary identifying factor for the payment method record to be used as the search criterion. If both VID, and merchantPaymentMethod are absent, account number for a Credit Card, account number - bank routing number combination for ACH/ECP, fiscal number used for a Boleto transaction will be used as the search criterion depending on type specified in the input PaymentMethod object. Since PayPal transactions processed through CashBox have no unique identifier, all PayPal transactions will be returned. Merchants should use the paging parameters to limit the number of records returned per call

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
paymentMethod - Payment method to use as search criterion
page - Page number to begin results returned. First page number is 0
pageSize - Number of results to display per page, should be more than 0
Returns:
array of Transaction objects - Array of Transaction objects matching the search criteria
Throws:
VindiciaReturnException - for non-200 return codes from Vindicia
VindiciaServiceException

score

public TransactionScoreReturn score(java.lang.String srd)
                             throws VindiciaReturnException,
                                    VindiciaServiceException
Evaluates chargeback risk score (fraud score) for the input transaction. The transaction must have billing city, billing state, billing country, and IP address at the mininum. The risk score can range for 0 (no risk) to 100 (almost certain that the transaction will result into a chargeback). This call also records the transaction in the Vindicia database.

Parameters:
srd - sparse return descriptor
Returns:
TransactionScoreReturn - custom return bean class for this method
Throws:
VindiciaReturnException - for non-200 return codes from Vindicia
